Harvest's End

As golden fields give way to rest,  
    The harvest moon looms bright;  
With every sheaf, we’ve been blessed,  
    In the soft embrace of night.

The last of summer's warmth drawn in,  
    A promise of the year;  
In every fruit, the tale begins,  
    To gather, hold them near.


- Doris Hedges
